urname was present in the medieval period, died out, and was then reintroduced from Scotland in the 17th century. It has been Gaelicized in Ireland as <b>Mac Iomaire</b> and in Scotland as <b>Mac Gumaraid</b>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":31,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":40,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William de Montgomery Lord of Ecton was born in 1184, in Little Cubley, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Ralph de Montgomery. He married Maud Matilda de Sutton before 1207, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1249, in Ashbourne, Derbyshire, England, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1184–1249":"1184–1249","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1160–1205":"1160–1205","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","Abt 1208":"umbes 1208","1160":"1160","before 1207":"enne 1207","1249":"1249","1205":"1205","after 1205":"pärast 1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1208":"1208","Cubley, Uttoxeter, Derbyshire, England":"Little Cubley, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ashbourne, Derbyshire, England":"Ashbourne, Derbyshire, England","Ecton, Uttoxeter, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1184–1249":"1184–1249","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1160–1205":"1160–1205","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","Abt 1208":"noin 1208","1160":"1160","before 1207":"ennen vuotta 1207","1249":"1249","1205":"1205","after 1205":"1205 jälkeen","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1208":"1208","Cubley, Uttoxeter, Derbyshire, England":"Little Cubley, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ashbourne, Derbyshire, England":"Ashbourne, Derbyshire, England","Ecton, Uttoxeter, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1184–1249":"1184–1249","1185–Female":"1185–Décédée","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1160–1205":"1160–1205","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","Abt 1208":"environ 1208","1160":"1160","before 1207":"avant 1207","1249":"1249","1205":"1205","after 1205":"après 1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1208":"1208","Cubley, Uttoxeter, Derbyshire, England":"Little Cubley, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ashbourne, Derbyshire, England":"Ashbourne, Derbyshire, Angleterre","Ecton, Uttoxeter, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William de Montgomery Lo